00:54:39.760 --> 00:54:42.230
You know, he was well to do.

00:54:42.230 --> 00:54:44.320 position:56%
In fact, he was one of the most well

00:54:44.320 --> 00:54:48.590
to do black Americans
in Washington for sure.

00:54:48.590 --> 00:54:54.390
And as I mentioned, he never relied
on his Library of Congress salary

00:54:54.390 --> 00:54:58.670
and instead he was very savvy
in acquiring real estate.

00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:01.830
And you look at the original black
leader in Washington- we're talking

00:55:01.830 --> 00:55:05.290
about what some of you would
be familiar names like Cooke

00:55:05.290 --> 00:55:09.810
and Syfax and Brent and Wormley.

00:55:09.810 --> 00:55:12.180
These were people who
were here early.

00:55:12.180 --> 00:55:18.850 position:56%
They had a leg up and that
included the opportunity to buy land

00:55:18.850 --> 00:55:21.700 position:56%
that later became prime real estate.

00:55:21.700 --> 00:55:25.860 position:56%
Murray came here right after the war
and he had those early pickings too.

00:55:25.860 --> 00:55:28.450
He also invested in
stocks and bonds.

00:55:28.450 --> 00:55:30.020
He had numerous houses.

00:55:30.020 --> 00:55:32.870 position:56%
He was both a building entrepreneur.

00:55:32.870 --> 00:55:36.310
He hired 50 black men
at any one time.

00:55:36.310 --> 00:55:41.940
And his father in law and his
mother was his construction foremen

00:55:41.940 --> 00:55:45.920
and he built way well over
100 structures in Washington-

00:55:45.920 --> 00:55:50.230
