friends like Pinckney Pinchback.

00:55:50.230 --> 00:55:52.750
Sometimes they were spec houses.

00:55:52.750 --> 00:55:58.930
In one case, he built three
houses near Logan Circle.

00:55:58.930 --> 00:56:02.370
One for himself and two to rent.

00:56:02.370 --> 00:56:05.860
In the end, once he built
his house on S Street,

00:56:05.860 --> 00:56:07.380
he rented all three of those.

00:56:07.380 --> 00:56:10.490
He also had properties in Maryland.

00:56:10.490 --> 00:56:15.510
So, he was a savvy investor
and given the stall that he had

00:56:15.510 --> 00:56:19.720
in salary at the Library of
Congress, that served him well.

00:56:26.180 --> 00:56:28.560
&gt;&gt;AUDIENCE MEMBER: (inaudible)

00:57:03.480 --> 00:57:07.320
&gt;&gt;ELIZABETH: Well, I'm going to
talk a little bit more about Murray

00:57:07.320 --> 00:57:12.180
and his cohorts and their
efforts to make change-

00:57:12.180 --> 00:57:16.040
both politically and otherwise.

00:57:16.040 --> 00:57:20.310 position:56%
I do want to mention first, his
association with the Board of Trade.

00:57:20.310 --> 00:57:25.030
That was a very influential body
given the government in Washington.

00:57:25.030 --> 00:57:27.470
And Murray, as I think I mentioned,

00:57:27.470 --> 00:57:30.800
was the first African American
elected to the Board of Trade

00:57:30.800 --> 00:57:34.560
and did you know that the
number of blacks increased,

00:57:34.560 --> 00:57:38.860
but it never kept pace
with the overall increase

00:57:38.860 --> 00:57:41.240
of numbers on the Board of Trade.

00:57:41.240 --> 00:57:45.540
And then there were fewer
and fewer African Americans-

00:57:45.540 --> 00:57:51.900
not only proportionally, but Daniel
Murray was part of that Board

00:57:51.900 --> 00:57:55.160
of Trade until he died in 1925.

00:57:55.160 --> 00:57:59.460
I think he may well again of
been the only African American

00:57:59.460 --> 00:58:01.580
on the Board of Trade
at the end of his life.

00:58:01.580 --> 00:58:05.300
Well, there were two issues that he
was compassionate about and worked

00:58:05.300 --> 00:58:09.910 position:56%
on the Board of Trade and got to see
ultimately after decades of effort,

00:58:09.910 --> 00:58:11.540
success with both of them.

00:58:11.540 --> 00:58:17.830
One was to establish in Washington,
manual trade high schools.

00:58:17.830 --> 00:58:22.820 position:56%
Manual education I call it, I should
say because Murray was very sure

00:58:22.820 --> 00:58:25.730
that this wasn't about
training for trades,

00:58:25.730 --> 00:58:29.900
this was about acquiring
an employing both the head

00:58:29.900 --> 00:58:33.080
and the hands to understand
drawings and to be able

00:58:33.080 --> 00:58:37.720
to manufacture something
from you know, two dimensions

00:58:37.720 --> 00:58:39.930
to three dimensions and so on.

00:58:39.930 --> 00:58:43.320
And eventually, he and the
other members of the Board

00:58:43.320 --> 00:58:46.980
of Trade were able to see two
such high schools established

00:58:46.980 --> 00:58:50.960
in Washington and one for
white pupils and Armstrong

00:58:50.960 --> 00:58:54.760
for black pupils and Anna's
brother, Bruce Evans was principal

00:58:54.760 --> 00:58:56.070
of Armstrong for many years.

00:58:56.070 --> 00:59:00.080
And the other was, to
establish in Washington,

00:59:00.080 --> 00:59:04.410
a free public library open to all.

00:59:04.410 --> 00:59:08.930
The Library of Congress books
don't circulate there of course

00:59:08.930 --> 00:59:11.390
and at this time they
didn't have extended hours.

00:59:11.390 --> 00:59:15.020
So, that was very important and
that eventually was realized

00:59:15.020 --> 00:59:21.430 position:56%
with what was initially called the
Carnegie Library Mount Vernon Square

00:59:21.430 --> 00:59:25.980
and of course lead directly to
the Marlin Luther King Jr Library.

00:59:25.980 --> 00:59:30.030
So, those were two, those were
two elements that he worked

00:59:30.030 --> 00:59:32.110
on that he could see
through to fruition.

00:59:32.110 --> 00:59:35.230
There were so many
others that he did not.

00:59:35.230 --> 00:59:38.790
You know, the National
Afro-American Council- some

00:59:38.790 --> 00:59:43.590
of the people involved
included T. Thomas Fortune,

00:59:43.590 --> 00:59:46.670
He was really the instigator.

00:59:46.670 --> 00:59:52.510
Along with Bishop Alexander Walters
who was the President for so long.

00:59:52.510 --> 00:59:56.660
And Murray interestingly
enough, he's not a lawyer.

00:59:56.660 --> 01:00:01.080
He was chosen to be the head of
the legal and legislative bureau.

01:00:01.080 --> 01:00:04.700
And part of the reason for that
is, over his time in the Library

01:00:04.700 --> 01:00:08.670
of Congress and at one point he had
been assigned to the law library,

01:00:08.670 --> 01:00:13.400
he had not only a self-taught
thorough grounding in law,

01:00:13.400 --> 01:00:18.810
but he gained much experience
writing legislation and he,

01:00:18.810 --> 01:00:24.150 position:56%
you know, whether it be with African
American supporters or whether it be

01:00:24.150 --> 01:00:28.480 position:56%
with white congressmen and
senators and he knew how to network,

01:00:28.480 --> 01:00:33.050
there were many cases where
legislation that was presented

01:00:33.050 --> 01:00:37.540
by a congressman or a senator was
in fact written by Daniel Murray,

01:00:37.540 --> 01:00:41.640
including the whole e
tax plan for Washington,

01:00:41.640 --> 01:00:49.620 position:56%
DC- a change in the structure which
was another Board of Trade activity.

01:00:49.620 --> 01:00:52.920
But, again and again
Washingtonians had to fight

01:00:52.920 --> 01:00:56.990
against Jim Crow cars
coming into the city.

01:00:56.990 --> 01:00:59.800
They had bird-dogged
that issue because over

01:00:59.800 --> 01:01:03.380
